h4 Update

p.
    The path of the current node is stored in <code>treeview.current_node</code>

p.
    To get the checkbox states of all nodes, check <code>treeview.nodes_checkbox_state</code>

p.
    Additionally, the following methods are available:

p.
    <code>treeview.expand_all()</code>

p.
    <code>treeview.collapse_all()</code>

p.
    <code>treeview.search(text) // filter the nodes by text</code>

p.
    For each row you insert, you need to specify a row id. You you also pass an empty string ("") as id
    and the data will be assigned an auto id.

p.
    The data argument on the update function is a dict {column: value}, where column is the name of the
    column as defined by the headers (Table.params.headers)

p.
    If you want to change the nodes of the tree, you can edit the <code>treeview.nodes</code>
    object and then call the <code>treeview.draw()</code> method.
